            <h3 id="section-heading-h3">The Coast Guard</h3>
            <p>The United States Coast Guard is a unique service. It is one of the five branches of the armed forces of the U. S. During time of peace it operates under the Department of Transportation (Note: this is no longer accurate and as of March 1, 2003, the USCG operates under the Department of Homeland Security). During time of war, or at the direction of the President, it operates under the Secretary of the Navy. The Coast Guard is responsible for a number of missions, including search and rescue, oceanographic research, maintenance of aids to navigation, icebreaking, merchant marine safety, port safety, law enforcement and military readiness.</p>
